# Coding Standards

> L2 instruction module — loaded when working on code style, types, error handling, or testing.

## {{tech.frontend.language}} / {{tech.backend.language}}

- Use strict mode (`strict: true`)
- Explicit type annotations — no `any`
- Follow framework-specific style guides
- Maximum {{conventions.max_fn_lines}} lines per function

## Error Handling

Standard error format:
```
{{patterns.error_format}}
```

- Use appropriate HTTP status codes
- Log errors with context (never log sensitive data: {{domain.sensitive_data}})
- Return structured errors to clients

## API Design

- **Style**: {{tech.backend.api_style}}
- Use plural nouns for resource endpoints: `/api/resources`, not `/api/resource`
- Version APIs in the path when breaking changes are introduced: `/api/v2/resources`
- Use HTTP methods semantically: `GET` (read), `POST` (create), `PUT` (full update), `PATCH` (partial update), `DELETE` (remove)
- Return consistent response shapes — always include pagination metadata for list endpoints
- Paginate list endpoints by default: `?page=1&pageSize=25` or `?offset=0&limit=25`
- Use query parameters for filtering, sorting, and field selection: `?status=active&sort=name&fields=id,name`
- Return `201 Created` for successful creation with the created resource in the body
- Return `204 No Content` for successful deletion
- Include `Location` header on `201` responses pointing to the new resource

## Testing

- Minimum **{{conventions.coverage_target}}%** code coverage for new code
- Frontend testing: {{tech.frontend.testing}} | Backend testing: {{tech.backend.testing}}
- See [instructions/testing-conventions.md](testing-conventions.md) for full testing rules, patterns, and checklists

## Quality Standards

- Use actual project patterns from codebase (not generic examples)
- Include authorization checks for all protected operations
- Add audit trails for sensitive data changes
- Verify code against context files before proposing changes

## Confidence Scoring

When proposing changes, include a confidence score:

| Score | Meaning |
|-------|---------|
| **90-100%** | Verified pattern, minimal assumptions |
| **70-89%** | Sound approach, some uncertainties |
| **50-69%** | Reasonable but significant unknowns |
| **< 50%** | Experimental, needs validation |

**Skip for**: Simple factual answers, reading existing code, established patterns.

